=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_InRange_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.7877
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9420
  pitch_clarity: 5.2268
  inharmonicity: 0.0382
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.7326
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: InRange Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/InRange.html
// Tags: InRange, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// See the trigger
{ InRange.kr(SinOsc.kr(1, 0, 0.2), -0.15, 0.15) }.play;

// Trigger noise burst
{ InRange.kr(SinOsc.kr(1, 0, 0.2), -0.15, 0.15) * BrownNoise.ar(0.1) }.play;
